<div align="center" class="mtop35p"><h4><b>INTRODUCTION TO PANCHANGAM</b></h4></div>
<div class="row mtop45p">
<div class="col-sm-5">
<!-- -->
<div class="list-group">
<div class="list-group-item">
Panchangam = Pancha (Five) + Anga (Elements)
</div><!--/.list-group-item -->
</div><!--/.list-group -->
<!-- -->
<div>
The Five Elements of Panchanga are
<ul>
<li>Vaara (Week)</li>
<li>Thithi (Day)</li>
<li>Nakshatra (Star)</li>
<li>Yoga</li>
<li>Karana</li>
</ul>
and this five elements come to know based on the position of Sun and Moon.
</div>

</div><!--/.col-sm-5 -->
<div class="col-sm-7">
<div>Panchanga considers 7 Planets + 2 Shadowly Planets.</div>
<div><h5><b>Time taken by the Planets to move in the Orbit:</b></h5></div>
<div class="list-group">
<div class="list-group-item">
All the planets moves in forward - Clockwise Direction<br/>
Rahu and Kethu moves in Backward - Anti-Clockwise Direction (Vakra / Retrogression)
</div><!--/list-group-item -->
